<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-03-07T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-03-07T18:00:00-05:00" n="40" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d40">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">711.4515 Air Pollution/414:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Chargé in Canada (<persName type="from">Boal</persName>)</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-03-07T18:00:00-05:00">March
                                        7, 1933—6 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>9. Your telegram No. 7, March 1, 4 p.m. Express to Department of
                                External Affairs appreciation of Canadian Government’s willingness
                                to enter upon negotiations and inquire when Canadian representative
                                will be prepared to open discussion. Qualification referred to in
                                Canadian note may be discussed in course of negotiations along with
                                other questions which will arise.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>